Film4.uk.title: Deja Vu
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Pulsating sci-fi action with Denzel Washington and Val Kilmer. An AFT agent uses new technology to reach back in time, stop a ferry bombing, and save the love of his life. Simple.

Film4.uk.title: Man on Fire
Film4.uk.description: (2004) Revenge thriller with Denzel Washington. An ex-CIA agent who's trying to start a new life in Mexico seeks brutal retribution when the girl who he's been hired to guard is kidnapped.

Film4.uk.title: Hush
Film4.uk.description: (2008) Thriller with William Ash and Christine Bottomley. A man is drawn into a deadly and gory cat-and-mouse game of survival when his girlfriend is abducted by a mysterious truck driver.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Dragonball Evolution
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Martial arts adventure. Justin Chatwin stars as the leader of a mystical band of warriors who are out to save the world from the ancient demon Lord Piccolo. With James Marsters.

Film4.uk.title: Baby's Day Out
Film4.uk.description: (1994) Comedy starring Joe Mantegna, Joe Pantoliano and Brian Haley. Inept criminals kidnap a millionaire's baby. But when the boy escapes, there's mayhem as they try to track him down.

Film4.uk.title: The Seeker: The Dark Is Rising
Film4.uk.description: (2007) Supernatural thriller. Alexander Ludwig stars as The Seeker, who has the task of finding six items hidden throughout time, which the scary forces of The Dark are also looking for.

Film4.uk.title: Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Oscar-winning animated superhero adventure with the voices of Shameik Moore, Kathryn Hahn and Nicolas Cage. Can a gang of Spider-heroes save the universe from reality-bending chaos?

Film4.uk.title: Gemini Man
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Will Smith stars in Ang Lee's action-thriller as both an over-the-hill hitman and the young clone of himself sent to take him out. With Clive Owen.
(2023) Sci-fi action adventure starring Adam Driver as a spaceman who crash-lands on a strange planet where giant lizards stalk the darkness... 65 million years ago. Where on Earth is he?

Film4.uk.title: The Black Phone
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Horror with Ethan Hawke. Denver 1974 and The Grabber is snatching boys from the street. But he doesn't reckon on two kids with uncanny abilities who refuse to do as they're told.

Film4.uk.title: The Lovely Bones
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Saoirse Ronan stars in Peter Jackson's fantasy drama. The spirit of a raped and brutally murdered girl watches over her distraught family as her killer prepares his next attack.

Film4.uk.title: Barnacle Bill
Film4.uk.description: (1957) The final Ealing comedy stars Alec Guinness as the latest in a long and distinguished line of sailors, but there's a problem: he suffers from seasickness. So why not buy a pier?

Film4.uk.title: The Borrowers
Film4.uk.description: (1997) Family fantasy comedy-adventure starring Jim Broadbent and Celia Imrie. A family of miniscule people live beneath the floorboards of a regular-sized family's house.

Film4.uk.title: Tooth Fairy
Film4.uk.description: (2010) Family fantasy comedy. Dwayne Johnson stars as a tough ice hockey player who is transformed into a real-life fairy as punishment for telling a child that tooth fairies don't exist.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies Interview Special
Film4.uk.description: Director Steven Spielberg and stars Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance talk about making their Cold War espionage drama.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: Bumblebee
Film4.uk.description: (2018) High-octane sci-fi action adventure starring Hailee Steinfeld. When Charlie drives home a clapped-out VW Beetle, she gets more than she bargained for: a huge robotic alien.

Film4.uk.title: Top Gun: Maverick
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Danger-zone action as Tom Cruise returns to the cockpit after 36 years. He's Maverick. He still feels the need for speed. And there's a near-impossible mission to fly. With Jon Hamm.

Film4.uk.title: Infinite
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Sci-fi action. Mark Wahlberg discovers that his hallucinations are memories from past lives. There are others like him, but they don't all have good intentions...

Film4.uk.title: Paranormal Activity: Next of Kin
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Found-footage supernatural horror. A young woman visits an Amish community to make a documentary about her family. But there's a good reason why her mum got her away from there...

Film4.uk.title: The 300 Spartans

Film4.uk.title: Henry VIII and His Six Wives
Film4.uk.description: (1972) Historical drama with Keith Michell as Henry VIII, nobly supported by Donald Pleasance, Charlotte Rampling and Jane Asher. The dying monarch reviews his own life.

Film4.uk.title: Ride Lonesome
Film4.uk.description: (1959) Western. Randolph Scott plays a bounty hunter who has unfinished business with the brother of his latest target. But his quest for revenge looks like it could be undermined.

Film4.uk.description: (1949) This dark comedy from Ealing studios sees Alec Guinness take on the roles of eight characters, all the noble victims of a vengeance-seeking relative, played by Dennis Price.

Film4.uk.title: Land
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Wilderness drama with Robyn Wright. After experiencing a personal tragedy, a woman moves to the Rockies in search of isolation. But can she survive there?

Film4.uk.description: (2017) Fantasy adventure starring Matt Damon and Willem Dafoe. In 11th-century China, Europeans seeking the secret of gunpowder are caught up in a war against alien monsters.

Film4.uk.title: The Forever Purge
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Dystopian crime thriller sequel. The NFFA are back. The Purge is back. Racists feel empowered. And when migrants start to go missing in Texas, it seems like the Purge will never end.
